lead_paragraph: The local organizing committee for the upcoming Olympics in Rio de Janeiro said on Tuesday not a single case of Zika infection has been reported among 17,000 athletes, volunteers and staff during test events in the run-up to the games.

headline.print_headline: Zika-Free Warmups Suggest Minimal Risk at Olympics, Organizers Say
